				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: OT Gate hammer<a name="37646"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 2 04 8:44 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Well well well, this was the easiest valuable piece of equipment I have ever gotten.
<br />

<br />
I zoned into The Overthere.  I DE'd myself with the mask of deception.  I con'ed a guard there... dubious.  I cast my lvl 11 alliance song... amiably.  I started into the city.  He was not on track.  I moved farther in... bingo, now on track.  I was con'ing thing left and right cause I was a little scared.  I find him, con'ed him... amiably.  I then gave him a jade.  Horns go off... he gives me the hammer.  I make a B line back to the book.
<br />

<br />
It took all of 5 minutes.  Much satisfaction.
<br />

<br />
I am now just wondering at the practical uses of this thing.  I decide I am done adventuring someplace so I go start wacking on something till the hammer proc's me back to the overthere.
<br />

<br />
Do I need to be Dark Elf'd?  Will I get hammered (no pun intended) when I zone into the overthere in my normal half elf form?
<br />

<br />
I'd like some thoughts on that from people.</span></td>
